->///


-> App-Rexx Stuff

->/// "rexcom_export" "Export"
@node "rexcom_export" "Export"

Command     : Export

Action      : Start Fidonet (FTN) Mail Export

Parameters  : CLOSE/S

              Setting the CLOSE switch causes the Export window to be
              closed after the Export finishes. Otherwise it is left to
              the user to close it.

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_import" "Import"
@node "rexcom_import" "Import"

Command     : Import

Action      : Start Fidonet (FTN) Mail Import

Parameters  : CLOSE/S

              Setting the CLOSE switch causes the Import window to be
              closed after the import finishes. Otherwise it is left to
              the user to close it.

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_tofront" "ToFront"
@node "rexcom_tofront" "ToFront"

Command     : ToFront

Action      : Pop Monsoon screen to front (if Monsoon is running on
              a screen other than Workbench)

Parameters  : None

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_toback" "ToBack"
@node "rexcom_toback" "ToBack"

Command     : ToBack

Action      : Send Monsoon screen to the back of the screen stack (if
              Monsoon is running on a screen other than Workbench)

Parameters  : None

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_lockgui"
@node "rexcom_lockgui" "LockGUI"

Command     : LockGUI

Action      : Prevents some elements of the GUI from being updated while
              an ARexx script is running - most notably, the main message
              display.

Parameters  : None

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_unlockgui"
@node "rexcom_unlockgui" "UnlockGUI"

Command     : UnlockGUI

Action      : Returns GUI to normal interactive mode.

Parameters  : None

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///


-> AREA-Rexx Stuff

->/// "rexcom_aname"
@node "rexcom_aname" "GetAreaName"

Command     : GetAreaName

Action      : Returns the full name (as displayed on the area list) of
              the currently active area.

Parameters  : None

Result      : 0 for success, or 5 if message display window closed.

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_atag"
@node "rexcom_atag" "GetAreaTag"

Command     : GetAreaTag

Action      : Returns the short (or Tag) name of the currently active
              area. Only really of use for FTN areas.

Parameters  : None

Result      : 0 for success, or 5 if message display window closed.

@endnode
->///


-> GUI-Rexx Stuff

->/// "rexcom_progopen"
@node "rexcom_progopen" "ProgressOpen"

Command     : ProgressOpen

Action      : Opens a window containing a progress bar

Parameters  : TOTAL/A,TITLE/K/A,PROMPT/K

              The progress bar range always starts at zero with the
              upper limit definable using the TOTAL parameter. Use
              TITLE and PROMPT to set a title and progress bar
              text.

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_progclose"
@node "rexcom_progclose" "ProgressClose"

Command     : ProgressClose

Action      : Close progress bar window

Parameters  : None

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_progupdate"
@node "rexcom_progupdate" "ProgressUpdate"

Command     : ProgressUpdate

Action      : Update the progress bar

Parameters  : CURRENT/A,PROMPT/K

              Put the new position of the bar in CURRENT and a new
              progress bar text (if any) in PROMPT.

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_inforeq"
@node "rexcom_inforeq" "InfoReq"

Command     : InfoReq

Action      : Opens a requester

Parameters  : TEXT/A

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

-> MSG-Rexx Stuff

->/// "rexcom_saveascii"
@node "rexcom_saveascii" "SaveASCII"

Command     : SaveASCII

Action      : Saves the current message to a specified file as pure
              ASCII text. Note that if the LockGUI command has been
              issued the current message may @{b}not@{ub} be the one
              displayed in the main message window. It is therefore
              good practice to select the message you want to save
              using the MoveTo command before using SaveASCII.

              The NOHEADER switch can be used to exclude header data
              from the saved file. Kludges are saved dependant on the
              current setting of the 'Hide Kludges' switch.

Parameters  : TO/K, OVERWRITE/S, NOHEADER/S

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_firstmsg"
@node "rexcom_firstmsg" "FirstMessage"

Command     : FirstMessage

Action      : Jumps to message #1 in the current area.

Parameters  : None

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_getnummsgs"
@node "rexcom_getnummsgs" "GetNumMsgs"

Command     : GetNumMsgs

Action      : Returns the total number of messages in the current area
              in RESULT. If the message display window is shut then
              GetNumMsgs returns a result of 0 messages.

Parameters  : None

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_moveto"
@node "rexcom_moveto" "MoveTo"

Command     : MoveTo

Action      : Jumps to the specified message.

Parameters  : TO/A

Result      : Returns 0 for success, or 5 if the specified message
              could not be accessed.

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_curmsgnum"
@node "rexcom_curmsgnum" "CurMsgNum"

Command     : CurMsgNum

Action      : Returns the number of the current message in RESULT or
              0 if the message display window is closed.

Parameters  : None

Result      : Always 0

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_getfrom"
@node "rexcom_getfrom" "GetFrom"

Command     : GetFrom

Action      : Returns the name (or e-mail address) of the sender of the
              current message.

Parameters  : None

Result      : 0 for success, or 5 if message display window closed.

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_getto"
@node "rexcom_getto" "GetTo"

Command     : GetTo

Action      : Returns the name (or e-mail address) of the intended
              recipient of the current message. In a newsgroup area
              this command will return the name of the newsgroup.

Parameters  : None

Result      : 0 for success, or 5 if message display window closed.

@endnode
->///

->/// "rexcom_getsubj"
@node "rexcom_getsubj" "GetSubj"

Command     : GetSubj

Action      : Returns the subject line of the current message.

Parameters  : None

Result      : 0 for success, or 5 if message display window closed.

@endnode
